      reflection in the \(y\)-axis, the sign of the
      \(x\)-coordinate
      changes and the \(y\)-coordinate stays the same:
     \((x;y)\) →
      \((-x; y)\) or
      \(x' = -x\) and \(y' = y\), for example: (-3;
      4)→ (3;
      4)</li>

      <li class="Body-bullet-Left-indent"> For a
      reflection in the \(x\)-axis, the sign of the
      \(y\)-coordinate
      changes and the \(x\)-coordinate stays the same:
      (x; \(y\)) →
      (x; -\(y\)) or \(x' = x\) and \(y' = -y\), for example:
      (<span>-</span>3; 4) → (-3;
