      reflection in the line \(y = x\), the values of the
      \(x\)- and
      \(y\)-coordinates are
      interchanged: (x;
      \(y\)) →
      (\(y\); x) or \(x' = y\) and \(y' = x\), for example: (-3; 4)
      → (4;
      -3).</li>
